      description : "6.3 Ensure the Server Access Log Is Configured Correctly - 'httpd.conf LogFormat is configured'"
      info        : "The 'LogFormat' directive defines the format and information to be included in the server access log entries. The 'CustomLog' directive specifies the log file, syslog facility, or piped logging utility.

Rationale:

